                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <placeName>Montreal</placeName>\n                                        <date>Dec 7/48</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>\n                                        <addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Dear Friend</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">When I last wrote you I had not yet received<lb/>\n                                        our note of <date>31<hi rend=\"sup\">st</hi> October</date>\n                                        sent with the Occidents. It is to this that I<lb/> would now\n                                        reply. As I before wrote you I shall always be most\n                                        ready<lb/> and happy to do anything that my poor ability\n                                        will permit so as to<lb/> serve you, but even now I know not\n                                        what to do. You have <sic>authorised</sic><lb/> me to\n                                        receipt for you, <persName>Mr Joseph</persName> is your\n                                        agent for the Occident, and<lb/> as I believe, nay am sure,\n                                        does the needful there, A couple of subscribers<lb/> have\n                                        not paid their dues for the A of P. <persName>Mr\n                                                  J.</persName> says you ought to send<lb/> bills.\n                                        Knowing the amounts however I shall try &amp; collect for\n                                        you, I<lb/> certainly will endeavor to do my best to get you\n                                        new subscribers but I<lb/> think that\n                                                  conservatively<add>?</add> there are no more\n                                        religious readers here than<lb/> in other <add>in other\n                                                  צהלות with respect to the convention of which you\n                                                  speak</add>—with respect to the convention of\n                                        which you speak<lb/> more fully in your last I have to\n                                        remark that nothing would give<lb/> me quater<add>?</add>\n                                        pleasure than participating in a movement which<lb/> might\n                                        (and doubtless would) tend to promote the awfully\n                                        neglected<lb/> subjects of our much prized faith. Anything\n                                        that will agitate, arouse<lb/> our community from the\n                                                  <add>well known אורחות עולם</add> which now\n                                        enwraps and <sic>paralyses</sic><lb/> them, should be\n                                        encouraged by every lover of Gods people. My pen<lb/> as if\n                                        in spite of me runs on transcribing the declaration of the\n                                        wise king <add>דברי הימים למלכי וגו'</add><lb/> But though\n                                        my wishes would be with the project I fear I could<lb/> but\n                                        little promote it. Nevertheless I am prepared to take\n                                        part<lb/> in it, to do myself me the pleasure of taking a\n                                        trip to <placeName>New York</placeName><lb/> and to make the\n                                        acquaintance personally with <persName>Messrs\n                                                  Wise</persName>\n                                        <add>?</add> Thus you<lb/> see dear Friend I <sic>I</sic>\n                                        not only approve the plan if this were of any\n                                        <add>?</add><lb/> I am prepared to extend to at my best\n                                        support. God grant<lb/> that the movement (should it indeed\n                                        take place) may prove an<lb/> important one, and beneficial\n                                        to this and other generations “yet unborn”</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3m03zd6k/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
