              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3m03zd6k/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>I do not know that I should have any influence in creating in\n                                                  <persName>Mr Lyons</persName><lb/> a willingness\n                                        to join us. I have to write to congratulate him on the<lb/>\n                                        birth of his son, and shall then urge the matter, and invite\n                                        his<lb/> favorable consideration. What says <persName>Messrs\n                                                  Isaacs Leo</persName> &amp;\n                                                  <persName>Lilienthall</persName> what<lb/>\n                                        <persName>Mr gutheim</persName> and other Hazanim, Let me\n                                        know on response.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">When I can look over and finish it I will send you\n                                        an<lb/> translation of a chapter I made just before leaving\n                                                  <placeName>England</placeName> from\n                                                  <persName>Peutrol's</persName> well known\n                                                  <add>ועבד עמו כטוב בעיניך</add><lb/> I have\n                                        furnished it with rather long notes to defend him and\n                                        other<lb/> Hebrew authors from the attacks of\n                                                  <persName>Batnaye</persName> and others, the<lb/>\n                                        subject matter of this chapter relates to the history of\n                                                  <persName>R David</persName><lb/>\n                                        <add>?</add> the supposed ambassador from the Ten Tribes\n                                        more subtly related in the <add>חדושים</add>, will it<lb/>\n                                        suit the Occident, a Defence (such as it is) of any portion\n                                        of<lb/> our Hebrew writers I should say ought not to be\n                                        considered (by the<lb/> public) as out of place there! If I\n                                        do not hear from you<lb/> before it is finished (I am rather\n                                        busy now) I shall send<lb/> it you—<add>ואין קול ואין\n                                                  עונה</add>—</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">You acted as agent for the Voice of Jacob. Would\n                                        it be<lb/> too much to ask of you to forward me per\n                                        opportunity the<lb/> numbers <add>?</add> below. I have on\n                                        order from <persName>Dr Beuisth</persName><lb/> and assert\n                                        from <persName>Mr Difman</persName> to receive them\n                                                  “either...<add>?</add> money<lb/> or without\n                                        price, perhaps you <sic>dont</sic> know I made great<lb/>\n                                        efforts for the contrivance of the paper. When\n                                                  <persName>Franklin</persName><lb/> finally\n                                        retired, and that I was co-editor of the 1<hi rend=\"sup\"\n                                                  >st</hi> two<lb/> or three nos of the new series.\n                                        He wanted me much to<lb/> undertake it with <persName>Dr\n                                                  B.</persName> but I left\n                                                  <placeName>England</placeName> for\n                                                  <placeName>Montreal</placeName>.<lb/> I wanted\n                                        nevertheless the conservative paper such as it<lb/> was, to\n                                        continue. I may then at<add>?</add> for new numbers</p>\n                              <p>Pray don't be so long before you write, let</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3m03zd6k/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
