              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3m03zd6k/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>me hear how our projected convention gets on, and let's have all the<lb/>\n                                        <add>Hebrew</add> you can scrape together How gets on our\n                                        friend <persName>Bernal</persName>?<lb/> I wrote him some 9\n                                        months ago but <add>Hebrew</add>—I hope<lb/> he is well in\n                                        health and better in circumstances then when he<lb/> last\n                                        wrote. If you see him please tell him I shall be<lb/> glad\n                                        to hear from him and am surprised that I have<lb/> not yet\n                                        received a line from him. He does not appear to<lb/> be so\n                                        fond of writing now as when in <placeName>Montego\n                                                  Bay</placeName></p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Hoping that you also are in good health and<lb/>\n                                        “kicking” I am Dear Friend</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(10)\">Sincerely yours</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(11)\">\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">Abraham de Sola</persName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>By the way, I hear you were lately<lb/> in <placeName>New\n                                                  York</placeName>, hence you had a good<lb/>\n                                        opportunity to speak to <persName>Mr Lyons</persName> &amp;\n                                        others, Did you so</p>\n                              <p>The following are the nos of the voice with<lb/> which you will\n                                        please furnish me.</p>\n                              <p>43.48.50.52.53.54.55. from 57 inclusive to 72 from 73 incl<lb/> to\n                                        87.90.93.94.101.105.106.113 new series vol 1. nos<lb/> 20\n                                        &amp; 25. and of the last vol (vol 7)\n                                        2.4.5.6.11.12.14.16.17.<lb/> 22. and 24 to the end. I ask\n                                        you to supply me for the<lb/> sake of dispatch let me know\n                                        therefore at once whether<lb/> you can let me have them, if\n                                        you <sic>cant</sic> I will write at<lb/> once to my uncle\n                                        who printed them. that will take some<lb/> months before I\n                                        can get them in this way.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3m03zd6k/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
            }
